DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Characteristics which are necessary to allow a subject to participate in a clinical study, as outlined in the study protocol. The concept covers inclusion and exclusion criteria._An action or administration of therapeutic agents to produce an effect that is intended to alter or stop a pathologic process._Have a beginning, in a temporal, spatial, or evaluative sense; the point in space or time where something begins._A period of time that it takes for Earth to make a complete revolution around the sun, approximately 365 days; a specific one year period._A collection or single item of factual information, derived from measurement or research, from which conclusions may be drawn._Not known, not observed, not recorded, or refused.
